('31866', '1', 'In a pan large enough to hold all the ingredients, heat the oil over medium heat.  Once hot, add the chorizo, breaking up in the pan as it cooks, until it has released its oil into the pan and is fully cooked and beginning to crisp.'),
('31866', '2', 'Remove, leaving the oil in the pan, and reserve.'),
('31866', '3', 'Add the onion to the pan and cook for a few minutes until beginning to soften, then add the garlic.  Cook until the onion is soft, then add the spices and cook for an additional minute to marry the flavors.'),
('31866', '4', 'Pour in the tomatoes, chickpeas, and water.  Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes, then add the chorizo and cous cous and season to taste with salt. Simmer until the cous cous is cooked through and liquid is absorbed (depending on the size and brand of the cous cous, more water may be necessary). Allow to cool a little before serving.  Sprinkle with chopped parsley or cilantro, if desired.'),
('31867', '1', 'Heat a large skillet or soup pot over medium-low heat, and add the olive oil.'),
('31867', '2', 'Saute the onion, garlic, celery, and celery leaves, covered, until soft and colorless, about 15 minutes.'),
('31867', '3', 'Add the chickpeas and stock and bring to a gentle boil.  Simmer for 20 minutes until the chickpeas are soft.'),
('31867', '4', 'Remove half the chickpeas with a slotted spoon, and puree the soup in a blender, through a food mill, or with an immersion blender.  Return the puree and reserved chickpeas to the pot, and add the pasta.'),
('31867', '5', 'Cook until the pasta is tender, adding boiling water if necessary to loosen.  Season to taste with salt and pepper and the lemon juice.'),
('31867', '6', 'Serve with parsley or basil leaves and a drizzle of olive oil.'),
('31868', '1', 'Mix all ingredients together. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Allow to marinate for at least 20 minutes, preferably longer.'),
('31868', '2', 'Toast the bread or grill it for more dramatic presentation.  Spoon mixture on bread, drizzle with olive oil, and serve.'),
('31873', '1', 'In a large soup pot, heat the pure olive oil.'),
('31873', '2', 'Add the quartered yellow onion, carrots and halved celery rib and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('31873', '3', 'Add the drained chickpeas, the herb sprig bundle and enough water to cover by 2 inches and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer over moderately low until the chickpeas are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.'),
('31873', '4', 'Add a large pinch of salt and pepper and cook the chickpeas for 10 minutes longer.'),
('31873', '5', 'Remove from the heat and cool for 15 minutes, then drain the chickpeas. Discard the herb sprigs, onion, carrots and celery.'),
('31873', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a large bowl, soak the red onion in the vinegar for 15 minutes.'),
('31873', '7', 'Drain, discarding the vinegar. Return the onion to the bowl and add the diced celery, lemon zest, lemon juice, garlic, chopped rosemary, oregano and peperoncini.'),
('31873', '8', 'Add the chickpeas and olive oil. season with salt and pepper. Fold in the parsley and serve.'),
('31879', '1', 'Add squash and potatoes, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper, stir to coat, and cook until just tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('31879', '2', 'Add broth, chickpeas, tomatoes and their juices, and saffron, if using. Bring mixture to a boil then reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer until squash is fork tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('31879', '3', 'Remove from heat and stir in preserved lemon and olives.'),
