('31882', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('31882', '2', 'Add onion, celery, and 2 garlic cloves. saut 5 minutes. Reduce heat to medium, and cook 5 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently. Stir in tomato paste.'),
('31882', '3', 'Add wine. cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.'),
('31882', '4', 'Add water, grano, salt, and pepper. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.'),
('31882', '5', 'Add 1 teaspoon basil, chickpeas, and tomatoes. Cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('31882', '6', 'Combine the cheese, parsley, 2 tablespoons basil, and 1 garlic clove. Ladle 1 1/3 cups soup into each of 6 bowls.'),
('31882', '7', 'Drizzle each serving with 1/2 teaspoon extravirgin olive oil. top each serving with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.'),
('31897', '1', 'Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer for about 7-10 minutes.'),
('31897', '2', 'Add your cooked veggies and legumes and cook together another 2 minutes.'),
('31897', '3', 'Serve warm over cooked quinoa or basmati rice, top with fresh chopped cilantro and enjoy!Store in an airtight glass container in the fridge for up to one week. Its gets better each day since flavors sit together. Always reheat on the stove top.'),
('31899', '1', 'Place chickpeas in a saucepan. add 2 quarts boiling water. Cover and let stand 1 hour. drain.'),
('31899', '2', 'Place beans in a 6-quart slow cooker.'),
('31899', '3', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
