('31921', '1', 'Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in Dutch oven over medium high heat until shimmering.'),
('31921', '2', 'Add onions and cook, stirring frequently until sizzling, about 3 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened but not brown, about 10 minutes.'),
('31921', '3', 'Add eggplant, pepper, zucchini, and thyme. Season with salt and pepper and cook until vegetables soften, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('31921', '4', 'Add up to 1/4 more olive oil if pan looks dry or ingredients stick.'),
('31921', '5', 'Stir in tomatoes, cover pot, and reduce heat to low. Cook 30 minutes, stirring once or twice.'),
('31921', '6', 'Remove cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until thick stew-like consistency is reached, about 10 minutes longer.'),
('31921', '7', 'Add vinegar and season to taste with salt and pepper. Ratatouille can be eaten hot, warm, or cold but is best at room temperature.'),
('31925', '1', 'To prepare pasta, lightly spoon flours into dry measuring cups. level with a knife.'),
('31925', '2', 'Combine flours and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a food processor. process 30 seconds.'),
('31925', '3', 'Combine 5 tablespoons water, 1 tablespoon oil, and eggs, stirring well. With processor running, slowly pour water mixture through food chute, processing just until dough forms a ball. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. knead 6 times. Shape dough into a disk. Dust dough lightly with flour. wrap in plastic wrap.'),
('31925', '4', 'Let stand 30 minutes.'),
('31925', '5', 'Divide dough into 14 equal portions. Working with 1 portion at a time (cover remaining dough to prevent drying), press dough flat.'),
('31925', '6', 'Roll 2 dough portions into 18 x 3inch rectangles (turning dough over occasionally and dusting surface lightly with flour). Lay pasta sheets flat. cover.'),
('31925', '7', 'Combine chickpeas and next 6 ingredients (through 1 garlic clove) in a food processor. process until smooth.'),
('31925', '8', 'Place 1 pasta sheet on a lightly floured work surface. Spoon about 1 1/2 teaspoons filling mixture 1 1/2 inches from left edge of sheet. spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons filling mixture at 3-inch intervals along the length of sheet. Moisten edges and in between each filling portion with water. place remaining pasta sheet on top, pressing to seal.'),
('31925', '9', 'Cut pasta sheet into 6 (3 x 3inch) ravioli, trimming edges with a sharp knife or pastry wheel.'),
('31925', '10', 'Brush excess flour from ravioli. press gently to flatten tops.'),
('31925', '11', 'Place ravioli on a lightly floured baking sheet (cover with a damp towel to prevent drying). Repeat procedure with the remaining dough portions and filling mixture to form 42 ravioli.'),
('31925', '12', 'Bring 6 quarts water and 1 tablespoon kosher salt to a boil in a large Dutch oven.'),
('31925', '13', 'Add 6 ravioli to pan. cook 1 1/2 minutes or until no longer translucent.'),
('31925', '14', 'Remove ravioli from water with a slotted spoon.'),
('31925', '15', 'Place ravioli on a tray, making sure they do not overlap. cover and keep warm. Repeat procedure with remaining ravioli.'),
('31925', '16', 'To prepare pesto, combine basil and next 5 ingredients (through 1 garlic clove) in a food processor. process until smooth. With processor on, slowly pour 1 1/2 tablespoons oil through food chute. process until well blended.'),
('31925', '17', 'Serve with ravioli. Sprinkle with hazelnuts.'),
('31925', '18', 'Wine note: In this recipe, the key wine-pairing factors are lemon, nutmeg, and basil. A dry Italian white will pick up on the citrus and green flavors of the dish, contrast nicely with the nutmeg, and act as a crisp counterpoint to the softness of the ravioli. With this dish, try Mastroberardino''s Greco di Tufo. The 2006 is $ Karen MacNeil'),
('31929', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet or medium saucepan over medium heat.  Just as it begins to shimmer, add the garlic and crushed red pepper flakes and cook until fragrant, less than a minute.'),
('31929', '2', 'Add the chickpeas with a pinch of salt and cook for 5 minutes or so to soften them.'),
('31929', '3', 'Add the broth and tomatoes and bring the mixture to a boil.  Turn down the heat and simmer until the flavors merge and the chickpeas are soft, about 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('31929', '4', 'Add the basil sprig and most of the leaves, and continue cooking for an additional 5 minutes.'),
('31929', '5', 'Remove the basil stem.'),
('31929', '6', 'In the meantime, bring a pot of salty water to boil.  Cook the pasta until al dente, then drain, reserving some pasta cooking water.'),
('31929', '7', 'Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and toss well, adding a little pasta cooking water to achieve a creamy consistency.  Season to taste with salt and pepper, and serve with grated Parmesan. and remaining basil leaves.'),
('31930', '1', 'Combine the first 4 ingredients, stirring with a whisk.'),
('31930', '2', 'Dry chickpeas thoroughly in a single layer on paper towels.'),
('31930', '3', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet over high heat, and swirl to coat.'),
('31930', '4', 'Add chickpeas to pan, and stir-fry for 3 minutes or until lightly browned.'),
('31930', '5', 'Remove chickpeas from pan with a slotted spoon. wipe pan clean with a paper towel.'),
