('31977', '2', 'In a small skillet, drizzle a little olive oil over medium heat and add the chickpeas.  Cook for a few minutes until hot and creamy and just beginning to color.'),
('31977', '3', 'Add them to the bowl and allow to marinate and cool.'),
('31977', '4', 'Once cooled, toss the herbs and season again to taste, adding any remaining lemon juice if needed.'),
('31977', '5', 'Serve with the feta cheese loosely crumbled on top.'),
('31978', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('31978', '2', 'Add edamame, red pepper, and garlic. cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in 1/2 cup water, basil, chickpeas, and tomatoes. simmer 15 minutes.'),
('31978', '3', 'Add 1 3/4 cups water and salt. bring to a boil. Gradually stir in couscous.'),
('31978', '4', 'Remove from heat. cover and let stand 5 minutes. Stir in onions and feta. toss well.'),
('31979', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil.  Cook the pasta according to instructions on the box, shaving off a minute or two.'),
('31979', '2', 'Pour the olive oil into a skillet over medium heat.  Toss in the garlic and cook for 2 minutes.'),
('31979', '3', 'Add the bacon pieces and cook for 3 minutes or until they begin to render their fat.  Sprinkle in the red pepper flakes.'),
('31979', '4', 'Dump in chickpeas and stir to coat.  Then add the spinach leaves, and cook until wilted.  Season with a pinch of salt and add a half a cup or so of the pasta cooking water.'),
('31979', '5', 'When the pasta is done, add it to the pan with spinach and chick peas.  Cook, stirring constantly, for a minute or two.'),
('31979', '6', 'Remove from the heat, sprinkle with cheese, and serve.'),
('31980', '1', 'In a large bowl, toss chickpeas, onion, cucumber, mint, feta and parsley. In a small bowl, whisk lemon juice, olives, mustard, oil, and garlic together.'),
('31980', '2', 'Pour dressing on top of the chickpea mixture and stir gently until combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste, and feel free to add slightly more cheese, lemon juice, oil, salt, or pepper right before serving.'),
('31982', '1', 'In a large pot, combine broth, chickpeas, tomatoes, saffron, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cover. Bring to a boil. Once boiling, kill heat and set aside.'),
