('31982', '3', 'Add onion and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cook about 5 minutes, until onion is a little soft and translucent.'),
('31982', '4', 'Add garlic, ginger, and cumin. Cook for another 30 to 60 seconds, until fragrant.'),
('31982', '5', 'Pour chickpea broth mixture into saucepan. Simmer uncovered about 10 minutes.'),
('31982', '6', 'Kill heat. Stir in cilantro. If using spinach, stir that in, as well. Salt and pepper to taste. Spoon into bowls and serve with lemon wedges.'),
('31988', '1', 'In a 12- by 17-inch rimmed pan, mix potatoes, onion, rosemary, 3 tablespoons olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.'),
('31988', '2', 'Spread into a single layer.'),
('31988', '3', 'Bake on upper rack in a 425 regular or convection oven for 10 minutes.'),
('31988', '4', 'Meanwhile, oil a 10- by 15-inch rimmed pan. In a bowl, mix 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 teaspoons oil. Put sesame seeds on a plate.'),
('31988', '5', 'Roll drumsticks in soy mixture (add more soy if needed), then in sesame seeds to coat. Lay drumsticks well apart in pan. When potato mixture has baked 10 minutes, place chicken on lower rack in oven and bake until well browned (180 in center of thickest part), 30 to 35 minutes.'),
('31988', '6', 'When potatoes begin to brown at pan edges, about 10 minutes after adding chicken, turn with a spatula, moving unbrowned ones to edges. spread level.'),
('31988', '7', 'Bake until potatoes are tender when pierced, 15 to 18 minutes longer.'),
('31988', '8', 'While potatoes cook, put croutons into a heavy zip-lock plastic bag and coarsely crush. mix with remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil. When potatoes are done, mix in crushed croutons and bake until browned, 5 to 8 minutes.'),
('31988', '9', 'Arrange chicken on a platter with hash.'),
('31988', '10', 'Add more salt and pepper to taste.'),
('31995', '1', 'Light a grill. Rub the chicken with the canola oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill over moderate heat, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, about 30 minutes.'),
('31995', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, melt the butter.'),
('31995', '3', 'Add the onion and cook over moderately low heat, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('31995', '4', 'Add the plums and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until softened and nearly broken down, about 5 minutes.'),
('31995', '5', 'Add the red pepper jelly and mustard and bring to a boil, stirring until the jelly is melted. Carefully transfer the mixture to a food processor.'),
('31995', '6', 'Add the water and puree until smooth. Season the plum sauce with salt and pepper.'),
('31995', '7', 'Liberally brush the plum sauce all over the chicken and grill, turning the drumsticks occasionally, until they are lightly caramelized, about 5 minutes.'),
('31995', '8', 'Serve the drumsticks with any remaining plum sauce at the table.'),
('31997', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic freezer bag. seal and shake well to combine.'),
('31997', '2', 'Pour buttermilk into a shallow bowl. Dip 2 drumsticks in buttermilk, and place in bag. Seal and shake well, coating drumsticks completely.'),
('31997', '3', 'Place drumsticks on an aluminum foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Repeat procedure with remaining drumsticks. Sprinkle remaining cornflake mixture evenly over drumsticks on baking sheet. Lightly coat with cooking spray.'),
('31997', '4', 'Bake at 425 for 25 to 30 minutes or until drumsticks are well browned and done.'),
('31997', '5', 'Serve immediately.'),
('31999', '1', 'Position oven rack about 8 inches from heat source. Preheat broiler. line a broiling pan with foil. Pat drumsticks dry and trim off fat. Arrange in a single layer on prepared pan.'),
('31999', '2', 'Melt butter with garlic and lemon juice over medium-low heat. Season drumsticks with salt and pepper.'),
('31999', '3', 'Brush each lightly with lemon butter.'),
('31999', '4', 'Broil, turning often and brushing with lemon butter, until chicken is browned and crisp and has no traces of pink juices when pierced, about 30 minutes. Cool slightly.'),
('31999', '5', 'Serve drumsticks with dipping sauces.'),
('32005', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, heat the 1/4 cup of vegetable oil.'),
('32005', '2', 'Add the garlic and ginger and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('32005', '3', 'Add the chiles and cook until they turn dark red, about 2 minutes. Lower the heat to moderate, add the sugar, soy sauce, tamari, sherry and vinegar and simmer until the sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.'),
('32005', '4', 'Remove the sauce from the heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour.'),
('32005', '5', 'Strain the sauce and return it to the saucepan. Bring to a boil over moderately high heat.'),
('32005', '6', 'Whisk in the cornstarch mixture and bring back to a boil.'),
('32005', '7', 'Remove from the heat, stir in the sesame oil and scallions and transfer to a bowl.'),
('32005', '8', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('32005', '9', 'In a large pot, bring 3 inches of oil to 32'),
('32005', '10', 'Season the chicken drumettes with salt and pepper and dust generously with flour. Set a rack over a rimmed baking sheet near the stove. Working in batches, fry the drumettes until browned and crisp, about 7 minutes.'),
('32005', '11', 'Drain the drumettes on the rack and keep warm on a platter in the oven while you fry the rest. Sprinkle with the chopped peanuts and serve with the kung pao sauce.'),
('32006', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('32006', '2', 'Combine mushrooms, carrots, red peppers and cheese.   Pull away the skin from each drumstick to form a pocket.  Spoon the mushroom mixture evenly into pockets.  Secure with toothpicks.'),
